{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Madiga |poptime = |popplace = [[Andhra Pradesh]],[[Telangana]],[[Kerala]],[[Karnataka]],[[Maharashtra]] |languages = [[Telugu language]],[[Hindi]],[[Odia language|Odiya]],[[Tamil language|Tamil]] |religions = |related = [[Telugu people]],[[Hindi people]], }}
'''Madiga''' (also known as '''Maadiga''','''Maatangi''', '''Makkalu''', '''Madiga''' and '''Madigaru''') are a [[Dalit]] artisan group. They are classified as a [[Scheduled Caste]] and are found in the southern Indian state of [[Andhra Pradesh]],[[Telangana]],[[Karnataka]],[[Kerala]] and also found in Northern states of [[Maharashtra]],[[Chhattisgarh]],[[Odisha]],[[Madhyapradesh]] .<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/lf/2004/09/10/stories/2004091002370200.htm|title=Starring Madiga and dappu...|last=Madhav|first=K.V.S.|date=2004-09-09|newspaper=The Hindu|pages=02|access-date=2016-05-24}}</ref> Their socio-economic standing today has been improved through the impact of their classification as a Scheduled Caste. The Dalit activist [[Lelle Suresh]] made a critically acclaimed [[documentary film]] about the community, titled ''[[Mahadiga (film)|Mahadiga]]'', in 2004.<ref name=":0" />
