The '''Maragang''' or '''Kimaragang''' people are an [[indigenous peoples|indigenous]] [[ethnic group]] residing in [[Sabah]], eastern [[Malaysia]] on the island of [[Borneo]]. They reside in the [[Kota Marudu]] and [[Pitas, Malaysia|Pitas]] districts of [[Kudat Division]]. Their population was estimated at 10,000 in the year 1987. They are considered a sub-group of the [[Kadazan-Dusun]], as their language ([[ISO 639-3]] kqr) belongs to the Dusunic branch of the [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] language family. They are primarily farmers, raising paddy [[rice]], [[Cocoa bean|cocoa]], and cash crops.

