{{Infobox language |name=Momogun |altname= |nativename= |states=[[Malaysia]] |region=[[Sabah]] |speakers={{Sigfig|88,850|1}} |date=2007–2009 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[North Bornean languages|North Bornean]] |fam4=[[Southwest Sabahan languages|Southwest Sabahan]] |fam5=[[Dusunic languages|Dusunic]] |fam6=Dusun |lc1=kqr|ld1=Kimaragang (Marigang, Sonsogon) |lc2=tgb|ld2=Tobilung (Tebilung) |lc3=drg|ld3=Rungus (Momogun) |lc5=kzs |ld5=Sugut Dusun (?) |lc6=mqq |ld6=Minokok (?) |glotto=kima1244 |glottoname=Kimaragang |glotto2=tobi1239 |glottoname2=Tobilung |glotto3=rung1259 |glottoname3=Rungus }}
'''Kimaragang''' (Marigang), '''Tobilung''', and '''Rungus''' are varieties of a single [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]] of [[Sabah]], Malaysia. The three varieties share moderate [[mutual intelligibility]]. Children are not learning it well in some areas.<ref name=e18/>
''Minokok'' is an [[exonym and endonym|endonym]] of the [[Dusun people|Sugut Dusun]]. Their language may be a dialect of Rungus. Their number are not included in the population estimate at right.
